Nats=====True=====126
This Know Nothing politician left his position as Attorney General in the John 
Tyler cabinet in 1841 after Tyler refused to follow a Whig agenda. This senator 
authored a series of bills in 1860 which aimed to solve the impending (+) secession 
crisis by reviving the Missouri Compromise and fully compensating planters who lost 
their (*) "fugitive slaves." For the points, name this Kentucky statesman and namesake of a 
"Compromise" that failed to prevent the U.S. Civil War.=====
John Crittenden =====